14:09.348 --> 14:12.768
( Cheering )

14:12.810 --> 14:13.602
Look, all of them go!

14:13.811 --> 14:17.189
All our wishes upinto the universe!

14:17.439 --> 14:21.652
Merry Christmas bub,I love you.

14:21.652 --> 14:23.863
Merry Christmas you guys,Merry Christmas!

14:23.904 --> 14:24.738
Merry Christmas.

14:24.738 --> 14:25.698
Merry Christmas!

14:25.739 --> 14:27.116
Merry Christmas!

14:27.157 --> 14:28.534
( Laughter )

14:30.578 --> 14:32.288
Hey.

14:39.712 --> 14:41.797
Did you make a wish?

14:41.839 --> 14:42.798
Kinda...

14:42.840 --> 14:44.258
Good.

14:44.258 --> 14:46.594
And is the mojo back?

14:46.594 --> 14:48.220
I think so.

14:48.220 --> 14:51.473
Merry ChristmasSergeant McGuigan.

14:51.515 --> 14:54.310
Merry Christmas Olivia Young.

14:54.351 --> 14:56.437
Thanks for sharingyour day with us.

14:56.437 --> 14:58.480
It was wonderful, really.

14:58.480 --> 15:00.858
It was.

15:00.899 --> 15:01.692
I got to get her down...

15:01.734 --> 15:02.735
It's getting late.

15:02.776 --> 15:03.527
( Laughter )

15:03.736 --> 15:06.447
But if you think Christmas Evewas fun,

15:06.488 --> 15:09.617
wait 'til you see how we doChristmas day.

15:09.617 --> 15:11.535
Right?

15:11.577 --> 15:13.662
How can I say noto those faces?

15:13.662 --> 15:14.496
You can't!

15:14.538 --> 15:16.373
Alright, 0900 hours.

15:16.415 --> 15:17.458
That's 9 A.M.

15:17.458 --> 15:18.626
In the hotel lobby.

15:18.626 --> 15:20.794
Here, let me get your numberjust in case.

15:20.794 --> 15:22.254
Really?

15:22.296 --> 15:25.424
Well, yeah you... look,if it ain't broke...

15:25.466 --> 15:26.800
Go ahead.

15:26.800 --> 15:28.510
Here, alright.

15:32.431 --> 15:32.765
There!

15:32.806 --> 15:33.474
9 A.M.

15:33.515 --> 15:34.391
9 A.M.

15:34.642 --> 15:37.353
Alright guys, let's startto go, but not before...

15:37.353 --> 15:38.729
( Laughter )

15:50.658 --> 15:52.451
Now I'll get him.

15:52.493 --> 15:55.245
You got a call, from base.

15:55.245 --> 15:55.788
Oh!

15:55.829 --> 15:57.706
No, no honey!

15:57.706 --> 15:58.666
Sorry Daddy!

15:58.707 --> 16:00.209
It was an accident.

16:00.250 --> 16:02.294
Do you want to usemy new phone?

16:05.798 --> 16:07.633
No, it's okay.

16:07.675 --> 16:09.677
Captain...

16:09.718 --> 16:10.844
Of course.

16:16.725 --> 16:21.188
Yes sir, on my way.

16:21.188 --> 16:23.816
You've got to go,like right away?

16:30.239 --> 16:31.407
But it's Christmas!

16:31.448 --> 16:34.618
I know.

16:34.660 --> 16:37.830
But what about Charlieand Danielle and their mom?

16:46.004 --> 16:48.257
Alright.

16:48.298 --> 16:49.550
Her name's Olivia Young.

16:49.550 --> 16:51.218
Tall, blonde, beautiful.

16:51.260 --> 16:52.886
She'll be here at9 A.M. with two kids,

16:52.886 --> 16:53.679
a boy and a girl.

16:53.887 --> 16:55.222
Will you, uh, keep an eyeout for her?

16:55.264 --> 16:56.390
Give her that note?

16:56.390 --> 16:57.307
It's really important.

16:57.349 --> 16:57.891
No problem.

16:57.933 --> 16:59.727
Thank you.

16:59.727 --> 17:00.394
Merry Christmas.

17:00.394 --> 17:01.687
Merry Christmas.

17:14.950 --> 17:16.910
Thank you.

17:16.952 --> 17:17.828
Hi.

17:18.078 --> 17:20.329
Come on guys. This is goingto be so much fun.

17:39.475 --> 17:41.727
Hey, wait here a minute okay?

17:41.769 --> 17:43.729
Watch your brother.

17:46.523 --> 17:48.650
May I call up to aguest room please?

17:51.862 --> 17:53.947
Thank you.

17:53.947 --> 17:54.782
Thank you for calling

17:54.948 --> 17:56.450
the Fairmont Chateau Whistler Resort.

17:56.492 --> 17:57.743
How may I direct your call?

17:57.743 --> 17:59.870
Scott McGuigan's room,please.

17:59.912 --> 18:03.457
One moment please.

18:03.499 --> 18:06.376
Oh, it looks like that guest checked out.

18:06.418 --> 18:08.629
Checked out, when?

18:08.629 --> 18:12.299
About two hours ago.

18:12.299 --> 18:13.759
My name is Olivia Young.

18:13.801 --> 18:17.554
Did... did he leave mea message?

18:17.596 --> 18:20.682
No, I'm sorry, no message.

18:23.477 --> 18:24.853
Okay, thanks.

18:37.074 --> 18:38.659
( sighs )

18:38.659 --> 18:40.994
Okay guys, change of plans.

18:41.036 --> 18:42.704
Why, where is Hayes?

18:42.746 --> 18:43.789
And her dad?

18:43.831 --> 18:47.000
They had to leave,some family emergency.

18:47.000 --> 18:50.712
But it's Christmas and we,the three of us,

18:50.712 --> 18:53.882
we're going to havean awesome day. Right?

18:53.882 --> 18:55.676
Awesome!

18:55.676 --> 18:56.677
Okay, get your stuff.

18:56.718 --> 18:58.637
Come on, let's go.

19:02.850 --> 19:05.477
It's going to be fun, come on!

19:19.992 --> 19:20.534
Good morning.

19:20.701 --> 19:22.077
Good morning. Olivia!

19:23.996 --> 19:24.872
Good morning.

19:24.872 --> 19:26.123
Good morning.

19:28.166 --> 19:29.042
Olivia.

19:29.084 --> 19:29.877
Morning, Kim.

19:29.918 --> 19:31.003
Your office, now.

19:31.044 --> 19:32.379
Is there a problem?

19:32.379 --> 19:33.213
When you started last month,

19:33.422 --> 19:35.716
did I mention the Fort Wilcoxtoy drive?

19:35.716 --> 19:36.800
It's our outreach program,

19:37.050 --> 19:39.428
your predecessor took care of itand now it's in your hands.

19:39.428 --> 19:40.220
Oh, okay.

19:40.429 --> 19:42.556
In December, it isthis bank's public face.

19:42.556 --> 19:44.224
It's now your primary focus.

19:44.266 --> 19:47.603
And if Fort Wilcox is happy,our board is even happier.

19:47.644 --> 19:52.608
This will be your liaison atFort Wilcox, Sergeant McGuigan.

20:03.118 --> 20:04.453
I'm telling you the truth!

20:04.453 --> 20:05.746
Oh really.

20:05.787 --> 20:07.664
In this day of cloud computingand wireless backups

20:07.706 --> 20:09.416
and SIM cards, you actuallyexpect me to believe

20:09.458 --> 20:11.877
that my phone number gotcompletely lost in the ether?

20:11.919 --> 20:12.836
I had a flip phone!

20:13.086 --> 20:16.006
You saw it, there's no cloudbackups with those!

20:16.048 --> 20:18.884
I didn't know if you were okay,or if you just stood me up.

20:18.926 --> 20:20.761
I mean, I thought we werehaving a good time in Whistler.

20:20.761 --> 20:23.472
We were having a great timein Whistler.

20:23.472 --> 20:26.433
And I didn't know if you didn'tget my note

20:26.433 --> 20:29.686
or if you stood me up!

20:29.728 --> 20:30.979
But I still tried to find you.

20:31.021 --> 20:31.855
Oh, you did?

20:32.064 --> 20:32.940
Yeah, do you know how manyOlivia Young's

20:32.981 --> 20:34.191
there are in Los Angeles?

20:34.232 --> 20:35.317
Young is my maiden name.

20:35.609 --> 20:38.654
I go by my ex-husband's lastname Roberts for the house...

20:38.695 --> 20:39.947
the kids.

20:39.988 --> 20:41.823
Oh... of course.

20:41.865 --> 20:44.993
Look, I feel awful that youthink that I flaked on you.

20:45.035 --> 20:49.957
Can we just throw all that outand start fresh?

20:49.957 --> 20:51.583
When'd you guys move here?

20:51.625 --> 20:53.460
Uh, about a month ago.

20:53.502 --> 20:54.878
My sister Heather lives here.

20:54.920 --> 20:55.712
Oh.

20:55.921 --> 20:58.966
Remember those jobsI was applying for?

20:58.966 --> 20:59.800
Sure.

20:59.841 --> 21:00.926
This is the one I really wanted.

21:00.968 --> 21:02.970
So your Christmas wishcame true?

21:02.970 --> 21:05.430
Mmm... not all of it.

21:05.430 --> 21:06.682
Well what was the rest of it?

21:06.723 --> 21:08.642
Oh, we don't tell ourChristmas wishes

21:08.642 --> 21:12.104
until after they come true.

21:15.732 --> 21:18.819
Olivia... I'm a soldier.

21:18.819 --> 21:22.823
And when I get orders,I obey them.

21:22.823 --> 21:27.995
Even on Christmas Day.

21:28.036 --> 21:30.914
Look... we're going to beworking together a lot on this.

21:30.956 --> 21:34.793
That is still an open question.

21:34.835 --> 21:39.840
Well... if you decided thatyou want to be a part of it

21:39.881 --> 21:44.136
then you know howto reach me.

21:44.136 --> 21:47.597
And now you knowhow to reach me.

21:47.639 --> 21:52.144
( phone ringing )

21:52.185 --> 21:53.103
This is unbelievable!

21:53.353 --> 21:56.898
I mean... why doesn't thisstuff ever happen to me?

21:56.940 --> 21:58.275
Did he say if he hasa girlfriend?

21:58.317 --> 21:59.234
Did he mention it?

21:59.276 --> 22:00.902
I didn't ask,he didn't tell.

22:00.902 --> 22:01.653
Ugh...

22:01.862 --> 22:03.822
I'm not interestedin a relationship.

22:03.864 --> 22:04.698
You know what?

22:04.948 --> 22:07.868
Sometimes I just want tothrow something at you!

22:07.868 --> 22:11.747
( Laughter )

22:11.747 --> 22:13.749
I didn't mean to hit youin the face, I'm sorry.

22:13.749 --> 22:16.543
Yeah right.

22:16.585 --> 22:19.087
Is Danielle still mad at you fordragging her up here from L.A.?

22:19.129 --> 22:21.214
For putting her in a new schoolright before Christmas,

22:21.214 --> 22:23.175
for ruining her entire life?

22:23.216 --> 22:23.967
Yeah.

22:24.009 --> 22:25.927
Teenagers, so dramatic.

22:25.969 --> 22:29.139
There was no oneas dramatic as you.

22:29.139 --> 22:31.266
Don't worry about her,she'll be fine.

22:31.266 --> 22:32.184
Why can't I?

22:32.392 --> 22:34.603
Because you're too youngto stand in line all night

22:34.644 --> 22:35.312
to buy a video game!

22:35.479 --> 22:37.105
Kelly's mom is letting her go.

22:37.147 --> 22:37.773
Oh, wait!

22:37.939 --> 22:39.232
Kelly's in L.A. and we're here.

22:39.232 --> 22:40.233
How could I forget?

22:40.484 --> 22:42.944
I guess that just provesthat Kelly's mom loves her more.

22:42.986 --> 22:44.738
Or does that mean she lovesher less?

22:44.780 --> 22:45.781
You're not funny.

22:45.822 --> 22:46.865
I'm a little bit funny.

22:46.907 --> 22:48.075
No, you're not.

22:48.075 --> 22:51.119
Danielle? Charlie?

22:51.119 --> 22:51.870
Hayes!

22:52.079 --> 22:54.998
Wow! I thought I'd neversee you again!

22:55.040 --> 22:56.083
This is so random!

22:56.083 --> 22:57.250
Do you like,live around here?

22:57.292 --> 22:58.376
Yes!

22:58.418 --> 22:59.211
Really?

22:59.252 --> 23:00.253
Didn't your mom tell you?

23:00.253 --> 23:03.215
She saw my dad this morning.

23:03.256 --> 23:06.134
Hi Hayes, nice to seeyou honey.

23:06.176 --> 23:08.929
My dad said you never gothis note.

23:08.970 --> 23:11.390
Ahh, the infamous Olivia Young.

23:11.431 --> 23:12.349
Infamous?

23:12.599 --> 23:15.602
I was involved in the greatOlivia Young search.

23:15.602 --> 23:16.853
There was a search?

23:16.895 --> 23:18.105
I'll explain.

23:18.105 --> 23:20.273
I'm Jill McGuigan,Scott's mother.

23:20.273 --> 23:21.274
Pleasure to meet you.

23:21.525 --> 23:24.069
He felt awful about leavingWhistler like that.

23:24.111 --> 23:27.322
But orders come when theycome, it's the army life.

23:27.364 --> 23:28.949
Yeah he, he told me today.

23:28.949 --> 23:30.283
That must be difficult.

23:30.325 --> 23:32.160
I've never thought of itthat way.

23:32.202 --> 23:36.206
My father was a soldier,my husband, my son...

23:36.248 --> 23:37.999
I'm proud of them all.

23:37.999 --> 23:39.126
Of course!

23:39.126 --> 23:42.754
Well I'm glad that he foundyou finally.

23:42.796 --> 23:44.297
Anyway... I'm just...

23:44.339 --> 23:45.799
Come on Hayes!

23:45.799 --> 23:47.759
We have to go check out.

23:47.801 --> 23:48.635
Here.

23:48.635 --> 23:49.261
Lovely to meet you.

23:49.302 --> 23:50.637
You as well.

23:50.679 --> 23:51.680
Come on, Hayes.

23:51.680 --> 23:53.306
Bye Hayes!

23:56.184 --> 23:56.935
Okay, okay.

23:57.144 --> 23:59.187
I saw Sergeant McGuiganat the bank...

23:59.229 --> 24:02.649
he's the liaison for thisoutreach program I'm doing.

24:02.691 --> 24:04.401
I didn't tell you guysbecause...

24:04.442 --> 24:05.402
Because you hated him.

24:05.443 --> 24:06.319
No, I don't!

24:06.319 --> 24:08.280
Because you're mad at him.

24:08.321 --> 24:10.740
Well, I was...

24:10.782 --> 24:13.368
Well... he tried to find you.

24:13.410 --> 24:14.870
He left you a note.

24:14.911 --> 24:16.621
Doesn't that mean something?

24:16.663 --> 24:20.125
It does, butit's complicated.

24:20.125 --> 24:22.169
We need bananas,and apples.

24:22.169 --> 24:23.086
You already have apples.

24:23.128 --> 24:24.337
Well then oranges.

24:24.337 --> 24:25.172
Come on.

24:25.213 --> 24:26.339
Alright.

24:26.339 --> 24:28.008
No, I'm getting bananas!

24:28.049 --> 24:29.468
Punk!

24:52.908 --> 24:55.869
( laughs )

24:55.869 --> 24:58.205
♪ Repeat the sounding joy.

24:58.205 --> 25:00.248
♪ Repeat the sounding joy.

25:00.290 --> 25:05.921
♪Repeat, repeat, the sounding joy.♪

25:24.147 --> 25:26.191
Oh, toy drive.

25:30.070 --> 25:33.907
Oh don't worry, it fills upas we get closer to Christmas.

25:33.907 --> 25:35.283
With used toys?

25:35.325 --> 25:35.992
Oh no, no!

25:36.034 --> 25:36.952
Newer ones too.

25:37.202 --> 25:39.079
We collect all sorts of toysfrom local branches,

25:39.079 --> 25:41.039
enough to fill a warehouse!

25:41.081 --> 25:42.916
The base liaison handlesdistribution,

25:42.916 --> 25:45.460
it's quite the undertaking.

25:47.420 --> 25:49.089
Where are you going?

25:49.130 --> 25:51.174
We can do better.

26:12.028 --> 26:13.822
These are the ground rules,Sergeant McGuigan.

26:13.863 --> 26:15.949
Our relationship remainsstrictly professional.

26:15.991 --> 26:18.034
This is going to be morethan merely a toy drive.

26:18.076 --> 26:19.828
So we have 23 days to getthis done

26:19.869 --> 26:22.038
and I intend to make this thebiggest and best event

26:22.080 --> 26:24.124
Fort Wilcox and Coastal NationalBank have ever had.

26:24.124 --> 26:26.293
So, I hope you're up for it.

26:29.045 --> 26:31.298
Are you going to sayanything?

26:31.298 --> 26:33.717
Sounds like a big effort.

26:33.758 --> 26:35.468
Christmas used to meansomething to me,

26:35.468 --> 26:37.304
I want that back.

26:37.345 --> 26:40.974
Do you know why I joinedthe army?

26:41.016 --> 26:43.143
To serve your country,I suppose?

26:43.184 --> 26:45.145
Yes, proudly, but it'smore than that.

26:45.145 --> 26:47.063
I like the feeling of beinga part of something bigger

26:47.105 --> 26:48.732
than myself.

26:48.732 --> 26:52.319
That's why I like the glaciersso much.

26:52.319 --> 26:55.739
Is that why you're a liaisonon this?

26:55.739 --> 26:57.032
Christmas is importantto these families

26:57.073 --> 27:00.118
and I just want to be ableto help.

27:00.160 --> 27:06.124
So yes, Olivia Young...also known as Olivia Roberts...

27:06.166 --> 27:08.543
I am up for it.

27:08.543 --> 27:10.378
Okay.

27:12.672 --> 27:17.344
You know, Hayes was so excitedto see your kids at the store.

27:17.344 --> 27:18.386
Mine were too.

27:18.678 --> 27:21.973
Hard to believe they get soattached after just one day.

27:22.015 --> 27:24.100
Okay, so Christmas trees.

27:31.983 --> 27:34.069
I thought we were goingto the Christmas tree lot.

27:34.069 --> 27:37.238
We are, I just have to doa few things first.

27:40.450 --> 27:44.996
What exactly do you do here,in the army?

27:45.038 --> 27:48.041
Part of a unit,the Army Rangers.

27:48.041 --> 27:53.046
We are... on call, always.

27:53.046 --> 27:56.091
Wherever we go isn't discussed,nor is what we do.

27:58.927 --> 27:59.803
Olivia...

28:00.011 --> 28:03.306
the army and my unit, my countryand my family...

28:03.348 --> 28:06.101
it's all part of the same mixfor me.

28:15.568 --> 28:17.445
Hello!

28:17.445 --> 28:18.446
Oh, Scott!

28:18.738 --> 28:20.198
When I called you this morningI said there was no rush!

28:20.240 --> 28:23.701
Hey, you send out an SOS,I show up... with help.

28:23.743 --> 28:25.453
Help, what?

28:25.495 --> 28:28.498
Becky Fowler, Olivia Young.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.291
Nice to meet you.

28:30.291 --> 28:30.917
You too!

28:31.084 --> 28:33.169
Ooh! This little guy's a kicker!

28:33.211 --> 28:33.920
Aww!

28:34.087 --> 28:35.255
At least Joe willbe home soon.

28:35.255 --> 28:36.131
It's our first.

28:36.381 --> 28:38.049
Olivia's in charge ofthe toy drive this year.

28:38.091 --> 28:39.467
It's going to be morethan that.

28:39.509 --> 28:41.636
Awesome!

28:44.431 --> 28:45.598
Well thank you,this looks great!

28:45.640 --> 28:47.475
And I love the lights outside!

28:47.475 --> 28:51.438
When Joe gets back, he'sgoing to be so thrilled.

28:51.438 --> 28:53.064
Um... Scott, I bakedsome cookies.

28:53.106 --> 28:55.233
I put a dozen in each bagfor the two of you.

28:55.275 --> 28:57.110
Can you go grab them?

28:58.403 --> 28:59.738
Sure.

29:02.991 --> 29:06.995
I heard about you,last Christmas... Whistler...

29:07.036 --> 29:09.247
He felt reallybad about it all.

29:09.289 --> 29:10.498
You know about that?

29:10.540 --> 29:12.500
Yeah, my brother'sin the same unit.

29:12.542 --> 29:15.128
Got called away just likethat and they didn't come back

29:15.128 --> 29:16.963
until after New Year's.

29:16.963 --> 29:21.050
Wait, so do you really neverknow anything

29:21.092 --> 29:22.635
about where they'regoing or why?

29:22.635 --> 29:25.388
I've learned to connectthe dots.

29:25.388 --> 29:28.266
Do you rememberthose hostages in Syria?

29:28.308 --> 29:30.393
They were rescued andreunited with their families

29:30.435 --> 29:33.146
at the White Houseon New Year's day?

29:33.188 --> 29:35.273
Oh... yeah, I saw iton the news.

29:35.315 --> 29:37.859
Happy reunion,everyone in tears.

29:37.859 --> 29:40.528
I mean, I was crying andI just watched it on TV.

29:40.570 --> 29:42.489
It takes a pretty special teamto go in there

29:42.489 --> 29:46.117
and do something like that.

29:46.159 --> 29:47.994
Are you saying Scottand your brother...?

29:47.994 --> 29:52.415
It's never discussed,no public recognition.

29:52.457 --> 29:55.585
No press conferences.

29:55.627 --> 29:58.379
They're the heroesno one knows about.

30:06.054 --> 30:08.139
Grabbed an extra bagfor your lazy brother

30:08.181 --> 30:10.225
but I swear, he mightnot get any of them.

30:10.266 --> 30:11.851
( Laughter )

30:16.689 --> 30:18.107
Hi! Come on in.

30:18.149 --> 30:19.651
Oh, hey Sarah.

30:19.692 --> 30:20.360
Hey!

30:20.401 --> 30:21.361
Is that Joey?

30:21.611 --> 30:23.404
This is, uh, my neighbourSarah and her son Joey.

30:23.446 --> 30:25.949
I look after him sometimeswhen she teaches yoga.

30:25.990 --> 30:27.826
This is Oliviawith the toy drive!

30:27.867 --> 30:28.660
Hi.

30:28.868 --> 30:31.204
She's helping the kidsget toys this year.

30:31.204 --> 30:34.249
Do you know Santa?

30:34.249 --> 30:34.999
Well...

30:35.208 --> 30:38.044
Can you tell himI don't want any toys,

30:38.086 --> 30:43.341
I just want my daddy homefor Christmas.

30:43.383 --> 30:47.428
Hey... we're going to Skypewith dad when I get home, okay?

30:47.470 --> 30:50.390
Okay.

30:50.431 --> 30:51.683
Nice to meet you, Olivia.

30:51.724 --> 30:53.685
Bye guys.

30:53.685 --> 30:55.478
When does his fatherget back?

30:55.520 --> 30:57.105
We don't know.

30:57.146 --> 30:59.190
Two thirds of the baseis deployed

30:59.232 --> 31:01.651
and the family deploymentcenter is shut down.

31:01.693 --> 31:03.903
Budget cuts, so...

31:03.945 --> 31:07.365
it's going to be a prettytough Christmas for the kids.

31:07.407 --> 31:10.201
I'm going to try to change that.

31:10.243 --> 31:14.789
Sergeant McGuigan... let's givethem a proper Christmas.

31:14.789 --> 31:16.499
Yes ma'am.

31:16.541 --> 31:17.834
Thank you for coming.

31:17.875 --> 31:19.210
Oh, please.

31:19.252 --> 31:20.295
Enjoy those cookies!

31:20.336 --> 31:21.504
Oh don't worry, I will.

31:21.546 --> 31:22.589
Thank you.

31:22.630 --> 31:23.256
Bye.

31:23.423 --> 31:24.591
Tell Paul to stop being so lazy!

31:24.632 --> 31:26.634
I will, trust me!

31:26.634 --> 31:28.553
Bye guys.

31:34.434 --> 31:35.351
Awful!

31:35.393 --> 31:36.477
( Laughter )

31:36.519 --> 31:37.353
Good day!

31:37.395 --> 31:38.438
Your sister's cookies.

31:38.438 --> 31:39.689
Oh, thank you.

31:39.731 --> 31:41.691
Olivia, this is Paul.

31:41.691 --> 31:42.525
Hi.

31:42.734 --> 31:43.735
Olivia is in charge ofthe toy drive this year.

31:44.152 --> 31:46.446
Oh great, well if you needhelp with anything just ask.

31:46.446 --> 31:48.156
Perfect, thank you!

31:48.197 --> 31:49.240
Hey, did you get my text?

31:49.490 --> 31:51.784
Captain wants you at S.R. Inteleven though you're down.

31:51.826 --> 31:52.660
Copy that.

31:52.702 --> 31:53.536
Alright.

31:53.745 --> 31:54.746
And your sister saysstop being so lazy.

31:54.787 --> 31:56.456
( Laughter )

31:56.456 --> 31:57.290
Nice to meet you.

31:57.332 --> 31:58.750
You too.

32:00.460 --> 32:02.337
So I guess I can't ask howhe broke his leg, can I?

32:02.378 --> 32:03.796
Sure, playing basketball.

32:03.796 --> 32:05.632
Is that the truth?

32:05.673 --> 32:06.799
Paul's an unbelievable soldier.

32:07.091 --> 32:10.470
I'd trust him with my life,but not on a basketball court.

32:10.470 --> 32:13.640
This is where he brokehis leg, in this gym.

32:13.681 --> 32:15.558
Okay?

32:17.644 --> 32:21.481
What you do, what you don't talkabout, doesn't scare you?

32:21.481 --> 32:26.653
Of course it does, butI don't let it stop me.

32:26.653 --> 32:32.075
And I do talk about it,just not out loud.

32:32.116 --> 32:33.201
You know, I have this placethat I go

32:33.242 --> 32:36.829
that helps me sortsome things out.

32:36.829 --> 32:39.540
I'll show you,maybe you'd like it.

32:46.673 --> 32:49.676
I come here before andafter every mission,

32:49.676 --> 32:52.178
and sometimes in between.

32:52.220 --> 32:54.889
It's been a long timesince I've been in a church.

32:58.101 --> 33:01.646
What if I don't...really believe anymore?

33:01.688 --> 33:06.025
Well... we all gofor different reasons.

33:06.025 --> 33:10.863
We don't have to go in if itmakes you uncomfortable.

33:10.863 --> 33:20.873
( organ music playing )♪

33:21.124 --> 33:31.134
( organ music playing )♪

33:41.144 --> 33:51.154
( organ music playing )♪

34:01.164 --> 34:10.465
( organ music playing )♪

34:10.465 --> 34:12.675
( TV News ) In Kabul, as tensions escalate,

34:12.717 --> 34:15.219
the Secretary of State will be holding

34:15.261 --> 34:16.554
a press conference tomorrow.

34:21.516 --> 34:24.020
I know where you were today.

34:24.061 --> 34:25.772
What do you mean?

34:25.813 --> 34:27.648
Hayes texted me.

34:27.690 --> 34:31.860
She said you were withher dad... all day long.

34:31.902 --> 34:34.447
Don't read anything into that.

34:34.447 --> 34:35.989
We're working together.

34:36.032 --> 34:37.824
( chuckles )

34:37.824 --> 34:38.993
What?

34:39.034 --> 34:41.036
I know you like him.

34:41.079 --> 34:42.955
Have some fun!

34:42.996 --> 34:45.458
God, you can be soboring sometimes.

34:45.458 --> 34:48.543
Don't you have homeworkto do?

34:48.585 --> 34:49.879
Has he asked you out?

34:49.920 --> 34:55.510
No! And I'm too busy anyway.

34:55.551 --> 35:00.807
Hey... so, you're not mad atme anymore for making this move?

35:00.807 --> 35:02.850
No, I'm not mad.

35:02.892 --> 35:05.394
I'd like if we could spendChristmas at home this year

35:05.436 --> 35:08.314
like a real family.

35:08.314 --> 35:10.900
I like this house.

35:10.900 --> 35:13.444
Are you ever goingto finish unpacking?

35:13.486 --> 35:16.114
( laughs )

35:19.492 --> 35:22.537
( Announcement ) The trees are moving fast folks, get them soon before they sell out.

35:22.578 --> 35:23.830
It's for the soldiersand their families.

35:23.830 --> 35:25.414
I mean, many can'tafford trees.

35:25.456 --> 35:26.666
We want to surprise themfor Christmas.

35:26.958 --> 35:29.418
Don't you think we owe them thatat least at this time of year?

35:29.460 --> 35:32.380
And in return, I will put upsignage for your business...

35:32.380 --> 35:35.007
in every local branch ofthe Coastal National Bank.

35:35.007 --> 35:37.635
And, and have each one ofour tellers say...

35:37.677 --> 35:39.637
Can I say something?

35:39.679 --> 35:40.763
Yes of course, please.

35:40.805 --> 35:44.308
How many familiesare we talking here?

35:44.308 --> 35:45.560
As many as you canhelp with.

35:45.560 --> 35:48.187
It's a lot of free publicityand good karma.

35:48.187 --> 35:50.690
Do you know how many people comeinto our branches every day?

35:50.731 --> 35:53.526
And just imagine the smileson those kids' faces.

35:53.526 --> 35:54.861
Okay, okay, okay!

35:54.861 --> 35:56.028
Let me check my inventory,

35:56.070 --> 35:57.738
see if there's somethingI can do.

35:57.780 --> 35:58.531
Thank you!

35:58.531 --> 36:01.033
Here's our contact info.

36:01.033 --> 36:02.076
Great, thanks.

36:02.118 --> 36:03.828
I look forward to your call.

36:05.037 --> 36:05.955
Okay, moving on.

36:06.205 --> 36:08.624
Grocery stores, toy stores,department stores...

36:08.666 --> 36:09.667
Sergeant, let's go!

36:09.917 --> 36:11.377
Hey, this is a pretty bigoperation you've got there

36:11.377 --> 36:13.337
in your head, isn't it?

36:13.379 --> 36:16.048
Operation Christmas,very good.

36:16.048 --> 36:18.092
I like that!

36:21.220 --> 36:22.638
Hey Mom...

36:28.978 --> 36:31.022
You hear back from them?

36:32.607 --> 36:33.941
Your mom said Hayes neededhelp with something

36:33.983 --> 36:35.735
at exactly this time.

36:35.776 --> 36:37.904
Is Hayes always so specific?

36:37.945 --> 36:38.613
Yes.

36:38.821 --> 36:40.907
Yes... But my momsounded strange.

36:40.907 --> 36:43.534
Something's going on.

36:46.537 --> 36:47.246
Whoa!

36:47.413 --> 36:50.666
Charlie... what areyou guys up to?

36:50.708 --> 36:54.587
Madam, sir...please come in.

36:55.922 --> 36:58.132
( Laughter )

36:58.174 --> 36:59.675
Oh...

36:59.717 --> 37:01.177
Oh!

37:01.219 --> 37:02.511
This is amazing.

37:02.511 --> 37:05.765
Welcome to Christmas dinnerin Whistler.

37:05.765 --> 37:06.933
Your coats please.

37:06.974 --> 37:09.018
So much work.

37:09.060 --> 37:12.939
One, two, thank you.

37:12.939 --> 37:13.731
Good evening.

37:13.940 --> 37:15.608
I'll be escorting youto your table.

37:15.608 --> 37:17.443
I can't believe it.

37:17.443 --> 37:18.778
Look what they've done.

37:18.778 --> 37:19.946
Yeah, it's pretty sweet.

37:19.946 --> 37:23.407
The best spot in Whistler.

37:23.449 --> 37:24.492
( whispers ) Don't be boring.

37:24.492 --> 37:26.077
I won't.

37:28.246 --> 37:30.248
Please... have a seat.

37:30.289 --> 37:34.585
( Laughter )

37:34.627 --> 37:35.962
Okay.

37:35.962 --> 37:37.838
The menu for this evening.

37:37.880 --> 37:39.966
Prepared by our executive chef.

37:40.007 --> 37:41.801
Ta-da!

37:41.801 --> 37:43.803
Oven roasted turkeywith stuffing,

37:43.844 --> 37:47.014
cranberry sauce, mashedpotato... our Christmas special.

37:47.014 --> 37:49.517
And for dessert we haveChristmas Yule log cake,

37:49.558 --> 37:52.645
followed by chocolate dippedstrawberries.

37:52.687 --> 37:54.605
Come on kids, let's getyour coats.

37:54.647 --> 37:55.439
Where you guys going?

37:55.648 --> 37:56.649
They're showing'It's A Wonderful Life'

37:56.649 --> 37:58.067
at the base auditorium.

37:58.109 --> 38:00.695
You two can help yourselves.

38:00.736 --> 38:01.862
Thanks Mom.

38:01.862 --> 38:03.864
Thank you.

38:03.906 --> 38:05.157
Come on, kids!

38:05.199 --> 38:08.286
And... bon appétit!

38:15.001 --> 38:17.086
This is incredible.

38:17.128 --> 38:21.549
Well... to, um...

38:21.549 --> 38:23.551
Whistler.

38:23.551 --> 38:25.302
Whistler.

38:29.640 --> 38:31.225
Oh... that's better.

38:31.267 --> 38:32.685
Out of the work clothes?

38:32.685 --> 38:34.020
Yes.

38:36.230 --> 38:39.567
Oh...

38:39.567 --> 38:40.693
You okay?

38:40.693 --> 38:43.904
Mmmhmm.

38:43.946 --> 38:46.741
Well we've got to admit

38:46.782 --> 38:50.244
that the kids set us uppretty brilliantly.

38:50.286 --> 38:51.829
Yeah.

38:53.456 --> 38:56.542
But an Islanders fanand a Kings fan?

38:56.584 --> 38:58.711
Clearly our kids knownothing about the real world.

38:58.753 --> 39:00.046
Clearly they know nothing.

39:00.046 --> 39:03.716
( small laugh )

39:03.716 --> 39:07.636
In Whistler I said I wasn'tinterested in a relationship.

39:07.678 --> 39:11.223
Oh, I remember.

39:11.223 --> 39:14.185
What about now?

39:14.226 --> 39:19.565
Well, I should tell you thatI have some issues.

39:19.565 --> 39:23.778
Yeah, well... so do I,we all do.

39:23.819 --> 39:26.530
I guess.

39:26.572 --> 39:30.701
All we really have is the hereand now.

39:30.743 --> 39:32.787
That's true.

39:35.081 --> 39:36.999
Why don't we...

39:38.876 --> 39:44.215
do something that we did not geta chance to do in Whistler.

39:44.256 --> 39:46.258
What's that?

40:15.454 --> 40:19.125
So? How did it go?

40:19.166 --> 40:23.671
It was wonderful, romantic...he's so sweet.

40:23.671 --> 40:26.048
It's been a long timesince I've felt so...

40:26.090 --> 40:27.007
Aww, finally!

40:27.049 --> 40:28.134
Is this thing straight?

40:28.134 --> 40:29.969
Sure.

40:29.969 --> 40:31.470
And it felt good.

40:33.973 --> 40:35.766
There's just one questionthat I keep asking myself

40:35.808 --> 40:37.977
and I don't want to seemlike I'm diving in too soon

40:37.977 --> 40:40.604
or jumping to conclusions,but...

40:40.646 --> 40:42.815
do you think that I'm upfor this army life?

40:42.815 --> 40:45.109
It's not for everyone,you know.

40:45.151 --> 40:47.236
It's tough.

40:47.278 --> 40:48.779
She seems the type of woman

40:48.779 --> 40:50.823
who's up for anykind of challenge.

40:50.823 --> 40:54.160
Yeah she seems it, but...

40:54.160 --> 40:56.162
Give it a minute.

40:56.203 --> 40:59.290
She wasn't born to this lifethe way we were.

41:02.168 --> 41:04.295
Come on, Scott.

41:04.336 --> 41:06.172
If this is meant to be...

41:10.426 --> 41:13.304
You're right.

41:13.345 --> 41:15.014
Thanks Mom.

41:15.055 --> 41:16.807
Mmm!

41:20.352 --> 41:22.354
Playing it safe getsyou nowhere.

41:22.354 --> 41:23.731
I mean look at me.

41:23.772 --> 41:25.191
I wanted to be a singer,remember?

41:25.232 --> 41:28.027
Oh in high school you werea star and then in college...

41:28.027 --> 41:30.696
Oh I chickened out,I played it safe!

41:30.738 --> 41:31.947
That is how this drama queenended up

41:31.989 --> 41:34.700
working at a lifeinsurance company.

41:34.742 --> 41:37.703
Oh, man... but if I couldjust sing again...

41:37.703 --> 41:39.663
that would be the dream.

41:39.663 --> 41:41.957
Well then you will sing again.

41:41.999 --> 41:43.083
Sing for me!

41:43.125 --> 41:45.377
Okay.

41:45.377 --> 41:47.254
Uh... Christmas carol?

41:47.254 --> 41:48.255
Perfect!

41:48.297 --> 41:50.674
Okay.

41:50.716 --> 41:55.346
♪ What child is thiswho lay to rest? ♪

41:55.387 --> 42:00.809
♪ On Mary's lap is sleeping...

42:00.851 --> 42:05.940
♪ Whom angels greetwith anthem sweet ♪

42:05.981 --> 42:12.321
♪ while shepherdswatch our keeping... ♪

42:12.363 --> 42:14.156
( Laughter )

42:14.198 --> 42:15.407
( applause )

42:15.407 --> 42:16.534
Yay, beautiful!

42:16.575 --> 42:17.993
Thank you.

42:17.993 --> 42:21.080
You have given me abrilliant idea.

42:21.080 --> 42:22.206
Thank you, Heather.

42:22.248 --> 42:24.250
Yay!

42:24.291 --> 42:26.085
But what is it?

42:26.126 --> 42:27.795
A Christmas revue.

42:27.836 --> 42:29.755
We'll make it a part ofOperation Christmas.

42:29.797 --> 42:31.257
My daughter's schoolchoir rocks,

42:31.257 --> 42:33.425
my sister hasan amazing voice...

42:33.425 --> 42:34.426
I'm not so bad on the piano.

42:34.677 --> 42:37.346
And I'm really good at tellingpeople what to do!

42:37.388 --> 42:38.430
( Laughter )

42:38.472 --> 42:40.641
Okay, you're my assistant.

42:40.683 --> 42:42.101
See, there must be dozensof people on base

42:42.101 --> 42:44.395
who have all sorts ofdifferent talents.

42:44.436 --> 42:49.567
Christmas carols, skits,dancing... pure holiday joy.

42:49.608 --> 42:52.027
Well?

42:52.069 --> 42:53.779
At least it's something we cando while we're waiting to see

42:53.821 --> 42:57.825
if these stores or Christmastrees actually come through.

42:57.866 --> 43:01.120
And, I'd like this showto be a fundraiser.

43:01.120 --> 43:02.288
A fundraiser?

43:02.329 --> 43:03.289
Yeah.

43:03.539 --> 43:06.083
To raise funds to reopenthe Family Deployment Center.

43:08.961 --> 43:12.006
I'll talk to General Holt,but... I like it.

43:12.047 --> 43:12.840
Count me in.

43:12.840 --> 43:14.425
Me too.

43:14.466 --> 43:16.176
Thanks guys.

43:16.218 --> 43:17.303
I love it!

43:17.303 --> 43:19.888
I can't imagine General Holtsaying no.

43:19.930 --> 43:22.016
That guy sings in a barbershopquartet,

43:22.057 --> 43:23.601
he's a great baritone.

43:23.642 --> 43:24.560
So, you're in?

43:24.810 --> 43:28.355
Olivia, I'm married to asoldier... of course I'm in.

43:28.397 --> 43:29.982
I hope we can pull it off.

43:29.982 --> 43:33.736
What's this I hear youhave getting stores to donate?

43:33.777 --> 43:37.281
Ugh... we have spent the weekbegging, imploring, cajoling...

43:37.323 --> 43:39.825
and every single placehas had an excuse.

43:39.867 --> 43:41.493
Yeah, it's the economyor they already support

43:41.493 --> 43:42.828
this cause, or that cause.

43:42.870 --> 43:44.246
It just feels like we'vehit a wall.

43:44.288 --> 43:48.000
I've never hit a wall thatcould stop the army.

43:48.000 --> 43:50.419
My BFF Ann, from college...

43:50.461 --> 43:51.587
her dad owns Kramers.

43:51.628 --> 43:52.671
The department store!

43:52.671 --> 43:53.380
Yes!

43:53.422 --> 43:54.715
Clothes, shoes, toys,

43:54.715 --> 43:56.967
all made right herein our beautiful state.

43:57.009 --> 43:59.887
Can you call yourfriend now?

43:59.887 --> 44:01.388
I sure can.

44:06.643 --> 44:07.478
Hey Sarah!

44:07.519 --> 44:09.229
Ann, you're on speaker phone.

44:09.271 --> 44:10.105
Hey Ann!

44:10.147 --> 44:12.399
Let's talk Operation Christmas.

44:12.441 --> 44:14.276
I'm listening. Let's hear it.

44:15.694 --> 44:16.695
Shopping carts of food,

44:16.987 --> 44:19.323
bags of clothes for everyfamily on base, toys galore!

44:19.365 --> 44:20.240
Big wow.

44:20.282 --> 44:21.533
Sarah is amazing.

44:21.575 --> 44:22.201
You're amazing!

44:22.368 --> 44:24.203
Oh please, what Sarah did...

44:24.244 --> 44:27.373
She wouldn't have done anyof that if it wasn't for you.

44:27.414 --> 44:28.207
That's the truth,

44:28.415 --> 44:30.042
so can you please takea compliment?

44:30.042 --> 44:30.959
If I was so amazing,

44:31.168 --> 44:32.211
then Mr. Sweeney fromthe Christmas tree lot

44:32.670 --> 44:36.131
would've returned at least oneof my dozen phone messages.

44:36.131 --> 44:39.259
Um... it's probably morelike two dozen.

44:39.301 --> 44:41.387
( Laughter )

44:44.306 --> 44:47.059
I like this... us.

44:47.101 --> 44:49.436
Yeah.

44:49.478 --> 44:51.188
Nobody's around...

44:51.230 --> 44:52.398
Mmm!

44:53.607 --> 44:56.193
Hey guys.

44:56.235 --> 44:57.444
Hey Mom, what's up?

45:11.542 --> 45:12.626
Hey guys!

45:12.626 --> 45:14.253
Hey Scott!

45:14.253 --> 45:15.546
You did it!

45:15.587 --> 45:17.631
Hey, uh, you Sergeant McGuigan?

45:17.631 --> 45:18.924
Yeah.

45:18.924 --> 45:20.509
Mr. Sweeney saysMerry Christmas.

45:20.551 --> 45:21.593
Are you Mrs. Young?

45:21.593 --> 45:22.261
Yes.

45:22.428 --> 45:24.138
Mr. Sweeney saysstop calling!

45:24.138 --> 45:24.888
( Laughter )

45:25.055 --> 45:26.265
He also says you can'thave a tree

45:26.306 --> 45:28.434
without all the trimmings.

45:29.810 --> 45:31.270
Oh... Another three truckson the way.

45:31.270 --> 45:33.021
That's great.

45:34.440 --> 45:35.149
Enjoy!

45:35.190 --> 45:35.983
Thank you.

45:35.983 --> 45:37.484
Thank you.

45:37.526 --> 45:39.403
This is fantastic!

45:39.445 --> 45:41.905
Now will you take a compliment?

45:41.947 --> 45:44.074
It's amazing,you are amazing.

45:46.577 --> 45:48.454
Oh, they are going to beso happy.

45:48.454 --> 45:50.622
It has been a fantastic day.

45:50.664 --> 45:52.499
You were right...

45:52.541 --> 45:53.417
I was?

45:53.625 --> 45:55.085
Being part of somethingbigger than yourself

45:55.127 --> 45:57.045
is an incredible feeling.

45:59.214 --> 46:00.632
My choir director says we're in.

46:00.632 --> 46:01.633
That's fantastic!

46:01.633 --> 46:03.969
Can I be the wise man?

46:03.969 --> 46:06.764
I think there should bea wise woman in there.

46:06.805 --> 46:08.348
And that's me!

46:08.390 --> 46:09.600
Excuse me...

46:09.641 --> 46:11.143
McGuigan.

46:11.185 --> 46:12.144
Yes, Captain.

46:12.186 --> 46:13.604
Do you sing Mrs. McGuigan?

46:13.645 --> 46:16.315
Oh... no, no... tone deaf.

46:16.356 --> 46:19.276
But I am good at sewing soI can help with the costumes.

46:19.318 --> 46:21.111
That would be great,thank you.

46:21.111 --> 46:22.279
This is going to beso much fun.

46:22.321 --> 46:23.197
Mmmhmmm.

46:23.197 --> 46:24.239
Totally!

46:24.239 --> 46:25.282
I still can't get over those trees.

46:25.324 --> 46:26.325
Yeah, Merry Christmas!

46:26.366 --> 46:28.118
I know, there's so many!

46:28.160 --> 46:29.453
It's going to bea great Christmas.

46:29.495 --> 46:31.622
I've never seen anythinglike it!

46:31.663 --> 46:32.623
They're endless.

46:32.664 --> 46:34.333
Yes.

46:39.338 --> 46:42.090
You've got to go,right now?

46:42.132 --> 46:43.800
I'm just on alert.

46:45.636 --> 46:47.679
And you can't say where?

46:47.679 --> 46:49.473
Or why?

46:55.521 --> 46:56.605
Hey... finish eating.

46:56.647 --> 46:58.524
I made your favourite dessert...

46:58.524 --> 47:00.692
lemon meringue pie.

47:11.703 --> 47:14.164
Alright, they're watchinga movie.

47:31.890 --> 47:34.351
This is what I do.

47:39.439 --> 47:43.110
Well we knew this time wasgoing to come eventually.

47:43.151 --> 47:46.613
Yeah...

47:46.655 --> 47:49.241
This life isn'tfor everyone.

47:49.241 --> 47:52.244
No... no it's not.

47:52.244 --> 47:56.957
But what it's taught meis to live in the moment.

47:56.999 --> 48:01.044
All we really have isthe here and now...

48:01.086 --> 48:03.422
so let's make the most of that.

48:16.268 --> 48:18.270
And tomorrow?

48:33.160 --> 48:34.036
You okay, sweetie?

48:34.244 --> 48:39.458
Yeah... just wonderingif you were okay.

48:39.458 --> 48:41.877
Oh honey, I'm fine.

48:41.918 --> 48:43.754
Come here.

48:50.427 --> 48:52.179
It's just been a long day,you know?

48:52.220 --> 48:54.264
Yeah.

48:58.560 --> 49:00.604
What are you singingin choir?

49:00.646 --> 49:02.856
I can sing it if you want.

49:02.898 --> 49:04.942
Yeah, I'd like that.

49:09.071 --> 49:13.241
♪ Angels we have heardon high, ♪

49:13.283 --> 49:17.829
♪ sweetly singing o'erthe plains. ♪

49:17.829 --> 49:22.250
( Both ) ♪ And the mountainsin reply, ♪

49:22.292 --> 49:26.546
♪ echoing the joyousstrains. ♪

