♪ Gloria

49:34.513 --> 49:38.600
♪ in excelsis Deo.

49:38.642 --> 49:46.692
♪ Gloria

49:46.692 --> 49:51.989
♪ in excelsis Deo.

49:52.030 --> 49:59.705
♪

49:59.705 --> 50:03.792
♪ Shepherds,why this jubilee? ♪

50:03.792 --> 50:08.130
♪ Why your joyousstrains prolong? ♪

50:08.171 --> 50:12.384
♪ What the gladsometidings be ♪

50:12.384 --> 50:15.887
♪ Which inspire yourheavenly song? ♪

50:15.929 --> 50:24.688
♪ Gloria

50:24.730 --> 50:28.650
♪ in excelsis Deo.

50:28.692 --> 50:36.908
♪ Gloria

50:36.908 --> 50:42.414
♪ in excelsis Deo.

50:42.414 --> 50:46.793
These past few days feltlike a military operation.

50:46.835 --> 50:49.755
Couldn't have done it withoutall those guys you enlisted.

50:49.755 --> 50:51.256
We've done everything!

50:51.256 --> 50:53.759
Trees, lights, gifts, food!

50:53.800 --> 50:58.847
And now we havea show to put on.

50:58.889 --> 51:00.766
You done good.

51:00.766 --> 51:02.726
We did good.

51:09.191 --> 51:12.277
Listen, I'm probably goingto have to leave soon.

51:12.319 --> 51:16.156
So we should maybe celebrateChristmas early.

51:16.198 --> 51:18.450
Are you saying you're notgoing to be back for Christmas?

51:18.450 --> 51:21.828
I'm saying I don't know.

51:21.870 --> 51:23.872
Or you can't say, won't say,don't say.

51:23.914 --> 51:26.458
No, don't make this harderthan it already is.

51:26.458 --> 51:28.710
I'm just confused, okay?

51:28.752 --> 51:31.630
I don't know how to feel...

51:31.630 --> 51:33.381
and I don't want you to go.

51:33.423 --> 51:35.133
I'll be back.

51:42.349 --> 51:43.016
Um... I should get home.

51:43.058 --> 51:44.017
Yeah.

51:44.059 --> 51:46.436
What about our early Christmas?

51:46.478 --> 51:47.604
I'll talk to the kids.

51:47.646 --> 51:49.106
Ok.

51:52.484 --> 51:54.528
Good day.

52:02.577 --> 52:03.620
Sergeant McGuigan invited...

52:03.662 --> 52:06.665
Mom... his name's Scott.

52:06.706 --> 52:09.417
Okay... well Scottinvited us to...

52:09.459 --> 52:12.796
I know, Hayes already texted us.

52:12.796 --> 52:15.465
Early Christmasat their place.

52:15.507 --> 52:17.467
Well how do you feelabout that?

52:17.509 --> 52:18.927
Charlie and I think it's cool,

52:18.969 --> 52:21.805
we get to celebrateChristmas twice.

52:21.847 --> 52:23.849
How do you feel about it?

52:23.890 --> 52:29.354
Mom, seriously...everything has a risk.

52:29.354 --> 52:30.981
Is he worth it?

52:31.022 --> 52:33.525
I say yes.

52:33.525 --> 52:36.653
And I also say that it'sokay to be scared...

52:36.695 --> 52:40.574
it just means you care.

52:40.574 --> 52:44.744
There's more laundryin the dryer, please.

52:44.786 --> 52:46.997
And when did you grow up?

52:50.709 --> 52:52.752
Oh, you've done it now.

52:52.794 --> 52:54.796
I have?

52:54.838 --> 52:56.756
( clears throat )

52:58.550 --> 53:01.553
And you can donate at any branchof the Coastal National Bank

53:01.595 --> 53:04.681
to support the troops and theirfamilies at Fort Wilcox...

53:04.723 --> 53:06.850
give them the bestChristmas ever!

53:06.892 --> 53:10.312
Let's get the family deploymentcenter back up and running.

53:10.353 --> 53:13.899
Coastal National Bank willmatch every dollar donated.

53:13.899 --> 53:16.610
This is Operation Christmas.

53:16.651 --> 53:20.363
So, Coastal National Bank willmatch every dollar donated?

53:20.405 --> 53:23.742
You said if you were out toemail the president, so I did.

53:23.742 --> 53:25.076
He liked the idea,gave me the go ahead...

53:25.118 --> 53:26.912
I CC'd you on allcorrespondence.

53:26.912 --> 53:28.830
Oh yes, I readall the emails.

53:28.872 --> 53:31.082
General Holt calledthe president of the bank

53:31.082 --> 53:32.626
to thank him himself.

53:32.667 --> 53:34.002
That's good, right?

53:34.044 --> 53:36.838
The Family Deployment Centerhelps soldiers transition

53:36.838 --> 53:39.007
between here and thereand back again,

53:39.049 --> 53:41.593
all while supporting thefamilies during deployment.

53:41.635 --> 53:44.012
General Holt startedit 15 years ago.

53:44.054 --> 53:47.849
To have it back would meaneverything to him.

53:47.849 --> 53:48.934
So I suppose it's onlya matter of time

53:48.975 --> 53:52.437
before you becomea manager...

53:52.479 --> 53:54.064
well isn't thatwhy you're doing this?

53:54.105 --> 53:56.733
No, actually...

53:56.775 --> 53:59.611
everyone at Fort Wilcoxis so selfless.

53:59.611 --> 54:01.613
All they do is give...

54:01.613 --> 54:05.659
they deserve a specialChristmas.

54:05.659 --> 54:07.535
Hmm...

54:07.869 --> 54:09.579
You know something?

54:09.621 --> 54:11.706
Okay.

54:11.748 --> 54:13.250
I like you.

54:38.942 --> 54:39.651
This is Scott.

54:39.651 --> 54:41.903
Leave me a message.

55:51.139 --> 55:51.806
That's not how you...

55:51.973 --> 55:52.932
show me how to use chopsticks.

55:52.974 --> 55:55.226
No...

55:55.226 --> 55:57.896
Like that...

55:57.896 --> 55:59.439
Yes, twist it.

55:59.439 --> 56:03.109
And you want to flip it up in one motion.

56:03.109 --> 56:05.278
Perfect!

56:05.320 --> 56:07.864
Mom, are you okay?

56:07.906 --> 56:10.950
It's time we finished unpacking.

56:10.950 --> 56:11.785
Right now?

56:11.993 --> 56:13.661
I jumped into all this stuffat Fort Wilcox

56:13.703 --> 56:15.747
and our own houseis still in disarray.

56:15.789 --> 56:17.791
Okay, Olivia...

56:17.832 --> 56:20.418
I need to feellike this is home.

56:20.418 --> 56:23.588
So tonight, we are going tofinish getting this place ready

56:23.588 --> 56:25.632
for the holidays. Okay?

56:25.632 --> 56:26.132
Yeah.

56:26.174 --> 56:26.674
Okay.

56:26.800 --> 56:27.801
Home for Christmas!

56:28.176 --> 56:31.596
But, I thought we were goingto Sergeant M's for Christmas.

56:31.596 --> 56:35.141
Oh... honey, we are.

56:35.183 --> 56:38.978
Early Christmas, we are.

56:39.020 --> 56:43.108
But he's leaving soon andwe need to say goodbye.

56:43.149 --> 56:47.070
I don't want to say goodbyeto Sergeant M.

56:47.070 --> 56:52.283
Me neither,but it's his job.

56:52.283 --> 56:54.786
It's what he does.

56:54.786 --> 56:58.123
So... everybody get a box.

57:03.837 --> 57:06.131
Here, let me take this little guy.

57:06.131 --> 57:08.174
This is not your size...

57:14.556 --> 57:18.935
I have to ask...how do you do this?

57:18.977 --> 57:22.355
Faith... keeping positive,

57:22.397 --> 57:25.650
other army wives and husbands.

57:25.650 --> 57:27.652
There's strength in numbers,you know.

57:27.652 --> 57:30.238
I don't think I have it in meto deal with army life.

57:30.280 --> 57:33.158
You guys are all so muchstronger than me.

57:33.158 --> 57:37.036
But Olivia, I can see thatyou love him.

57:39.998 --> 57:43.835
This life is so much differentthan I've ever known.

57:43.835 --> 57:45.962
I would drive him crazy.

57:50.175 --> 57:53.052
He's leaving soon.

57:53.052 --> 57:56.598
Rangers don't leave the baseto play games.

57:56.639 --> 58:01.394
You'll be on his mind,you need to talk to him.

58:11.905 --> 58:14.741
♪ Away in a manger

58:14.782 --> 58:18.620
♪ No crib for a bed...

58:18.661 --> 58:20.330
What time did Scott sayhe was going to be here?

58:20.371 --> 58:22.874
Soon, he's just runninga little late.

58:22.874 --> 58:25.376
He'll be here soon.

58:25.418 --> 58:28.254
Can we stop for a second?

58:28.296 --> 58:30.089
I was hoping for something,I don't know,

58:30.131 --> 58:31.966
a little more upbeat.

58:31.966 --> 58:34.093
How about "The 12 Daysof Christmas"?

58:34.135 --> 58:36.221
Yeah, and then every memberof the choir would have a solo

58:36.262 --> 58:39.182
and that would take thepressure off me a little bit.

58:39.224 --> 58:39.933
That'd be cool.

58:39.974 --> 58:41.809
Excellent idea, guys.

58:41.851 --> 58:44.771
Would you get them in hereand rehearse it?

58:44.771 --> 58:47.232
You know Mom, you're prettygood at this.

58:47.273 --> 58:48.191
Don't tell anyone

58:48.399 --> 58:50.485
but I have absolutely no ideawhat I'm doing.

58:50.527 --> 58:52.195
My lips are sealed.

58:54.447 --> 58:55.073
Hey Sarah!

58:55.114 --> 58:56.366
Hi!

58:56.366 --> 58:58.117
You're bringing reinforcements.

58:58.159 --> 58:59.077
The cavalry!

58:59.327 --> 59:01.913
May I introduce the fabulousFort Wilcox dancers.

59:01.913 --> 59:02.539
Love it.

59:02.705 --> 59:03.331
And these guys are what I call

59:03.665 --> 59:05.083
all-purpose dancersand singers,

59:05.124 --> 59:06.125
whatever we need.

59:06.167 --> 59:08.211
Fantastic, thank you.

59:08.253 --> 59:09.254
Becky, would you take themover there

59:09.254 --> 59:10.838
and assign them numbers?

59:10.880 --> 59:11.923
No problem.

59:12.173 --> 59:14.425
Then there's me... I've beenin six musicals, two dramas,

59:14.425 --> 59:15.843
an Agatha Christie mystery

59:15.885 --> 59:18.388
and I've even played Tiny Timwhen I was little.

59:18.388 --> 59:20.682
Sarah, you are extraordinary.

59:20.682 --> 59:23.059
So does extraordinaryget a solo?

59:23.101 --> 59:25.311
You should hear my versionof Santa Baby.

59:25.353 --> 59:26.271
Done!

59:26.271 --> 59:29.399
Yes, thank you!

59:29.440 --> 59:31.067
Okay...

59:34.362 --> 59:35.196
Sorry I'm late.

59:35.405 --> 59:37.323
I can't stay, we havea re-con briefing.

59:37.365 --> 59:39.117
How's it going here?

59:39.158 --> 59:39.784
Hectic.

59:39.826 --> 59:40.994
Yeah, I see that.

59:41.035 --> 59:42.328
Yeah.

59:42.370 --> 59:44.914
Um... you hear anything?

59:44.956 --> 59:47.458
Yeah, we leave tomorrow.

59:47.458 --> 59:49.252
It'll be okay.

59:51.045 --> 59:54.007
Sorry to interrupt,I need your help.

59:54.048 --> 59:55.967
It's the dancers.

59:56.009 --> 59:58.052
Go ahead, I have to run anyway.

59:58.094 --> 01:00:00.638
Okay, um... I need to talkto you at some point.

01:00:06.311 --> 01:00:08.938
And all of a sudden,there he was.

01:00:08.980 --> 01:00:12.442
Ben... my handsome,wonderful Benjamin.

01:00:12.483 --> 01:00:15.320
Home two months early...surprise!

01:00:15.320 --> 01:00:17.071
Of course, I lose it.

01:00:17.113 --> 01:00:18.865
With all of that mascararunning down my face,

01:00:18.906 --> 01:00:23.119
I looked like a blubberingraccoon.

01:00:23.161 --> 01:00:26.831
The reunions make itall worthwhile, don't they?

01:00:26.831 --> 01:00:29.792
I'm so excitedfor my next one.

01:00:29.834 --> 01:00:32.128
You'll be havingyours real soon.

01:00:32.170 --> 01:00:34.172
Actually, no.

01:00:34.213 --> 01:00:36.090
What?

01:00:36.132 --> 01:00:38.134
Yeah, um... I just found outthis morning

01:00:38.176 --> 01:00:40.011
that Joe and the squadron arestaying on

01:00:40.011 --> 01:00:41.596
for a few more months.

01:00:41.637 --> 01:00:43.181
Oh Becky, I'm so sorry.

01:00:43.222 --> 01:00:44.849
I know he was going to behere for the birth.

01:00:44.849 --> 01:00:48.353
It's okay, I'm just a littleemotional right now, so...

01:00:48.353 --> 01:00:50.521
We'll be here.

01:00:50.563 --> 01:00:52.106
Thanks.

01:00:52.148 --> 01:00:54.692
I know I can always counton you gals.

01:00:57.904 --> 01:01:00.406
Olivia?

01:01:00.448 --> 01:01:02.408
Olivia?

01:01:02.408 --> 01:01:03.576
You alright?

01:01:03.576 --> 01:01:05.078
Oh... yeah.

01:01:05.119 --> 01:01:07.497
Sorry, just tired.

01:01:07.538 --> 01:01:09.332
So much on my plate.

01:01:09.374 --> 01:01:12.418
Operation Christmas,the bank, kids...

01:01:12.460 --> 01:01:15.880
there should be more hoursin the day.

01:01:15.880 --> 01:01:18.341
You don't need to pretend,Olivia.

01:01:18.341 --> 01:01:21.511
You're one of us now,we get it.

01:01:21.552 --> 01:01:23.471
You're worried.

01:01:33.272 --> 01:01:36.234
Scott's a good man.

01:01:36.234 --> 01:01:41.447
He deserves the truth.

01:01:41.447 --> 01:01:44.242
I know.

01:01:47.662 --> 01:01:48.621
What is it?

01:01:48.663 --> 01:01:50.331
Whoa!

01:01:50.331 --> 01:01:52.625
It's a Morse code signal light,come here.

01:01:52.625 --> 01:01:53.418
Cool!

01:01:53.459 --> 01:01:54.627
It works!

01:01:54.669 --> 01:01:56.254
Look.

01:01:59.340 --> 01:02:00.508
Thanks Sergeant M.

01:02:00.550 --> 01:02:03.136
You're welcome.Merry Christmas, buddy.

01:02:05.805 --> 01:02:08.933
And Hayes, I made somethingspecial for you.

01:02:08.933 --> 01:02:10.643
Danielle, phone!

01:02:13.062 --> 01:02:14.021
Oh!

01:02:14.063 --> 01:02:14.689
It's an ornament!

01:02:14.856 --> 01:02:17.191
Look Daddy, it's so pretty!

01:02:17.233 --> 01:02:18.276
Thank you.

01:02:18.276 --> 01:02:19.235
You're welcome.

01:02:19.444 --> 01:02:22.572
Every Christmas Day we getone that has our name

01:02:22.613 --> 01:02:24.282
and the year on it.

01:02:24.282 --> 01:02:25.450
Then we put it on the tree.

01:02:25.491 --> 01:02:26.868
My parents started it withme and my sister

01:02:26.909 --> 01:02:29.954
so I carried on the traditionwith my kids.

01:02:29.954 --> 01:02:31.664
There's something to be saidfor tradition.

01:02:31.664 --> 01:02:32.415
Yeah.

01:02:32.582 --> 01:02:34.041
Come on Hayes,put it on the tree.

01:02:34.083 --> 01:02:35.168
Yeah, get a spot.

01:02:35.168 --> 01:02:37.044
Come on!

01:02:38.463 --> 01:02:39.630
Oh, that's a good spot.

01:02:39.672 --> 01:02:41.591
It's beautiful.

01:02:42.383 --> 01:02:43.760
I love you!

01:02:46.220 --> 01:02:47.597
I love you too.

01:02:50.183 --> 01:02:51.684
Merry early Christmas.

01:02:51.726 --> 01:02:53.686
Merry early Christmas.

01:02:54.979 --> 01:02:56.814
Well Danielle, you're up!

01:03:06.491 --> 01:03:09.202
Merry Christmas.

01:03:09.243 --> 01:03:11.370
It's okay, you can open it.

01:03:21.088 --> 01:03:23.633
Danielle took it at the glacierlast year.

01:03:29.138 --> 01:03:30.431
It's beautiful.

01:03:30.473 --> 01:03:33.684
Really, thank you.

01:03:33.684 --> 01:03:35.603
You're welcome.

01:03:38.689 --> 01:03:40.399
I don't want this to end.

01:03:40.441 --> 01:03:41.192
Well neither do I.

01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:44.487
No Scott, please...let me finish.

01:03:44.529 --> 01:03:47.949
For our kids...

01:03:47.990 --> 01:03:51.244
I don't wantthis to end for them.

01:03:51.285 --> 01:03:54.747
And they've grown so close,and...

01:03:54.789 --> 01:04:00.586
I want that to continue.

01:04:00.628 --> 01:04:03.589
But...

01:04:03.631 --> 01:04:08.719
I don't have it in meto live this army life.

01:04:08.719 --> 01:04:10.054
I, I, I... just don't.

01:04:10.054 --> 01:04:11.138
What, you're ending this?

01:04:11.389 --> 01:04:16.102
Two Christmases cut short,I mean it just feels like...

01:04:16.143 --> 01:04:17.186
it wasn't meant to be.

01:04:17.228 --> 01:04:20.356
I completely disagree.

01:04:20.398 --> 01:04:22.525
It feels so meant to be.

01:04:25.611 --> 01:04:30.616
Do you know what I seewhen I look at you?

01:04:30.658 --> 01:04:35.121
I see a hero andan amazing man...

01:04:35.121 --> 01:04:41.252
and I need you to know how muchI respect that.

01:04:41.294 --> 01:04:44.797
But I know what it feels liketo be left alone

01:04:44.839 --> 01:04:47.174
and I can't go back there.

01:04:47.216 --> 01:04:51.095
I can't be with someone whomight have to go at any moment,

01:04:51.137 --> 01:04:52.597
not knowing whereyou are,

01:04:52.638 --> 01:05:00.646
if you're okay or not, if...if you're safe.

01:05:00.646 --> 01:05:01.731
I just...

01:05:04.525 --> 01:05:07.612
So you're afraidof the unknown?

01:05:07.612 --> 01:05:11.949
Life is full of unknowns.

01:05:11.991 --> 01:05:13.576
I could be a school teacherand get in a car wreck

01:05:13.618 --> 01:05:15.620
on the way to work,it happens.

01:05:15.620 --> 01:05:16.329
Scott...

01:05:16.370 --> 01:05:18.164
It happened.

01:05:18.205 --> 01:05:19.749
To my wife.

01:05:22.168 --> 01:05:24.503
And sure, what I do puts mein harm's way a little more,

01:05:24.545 --> 01:05:25.922
I get that.

01:05:35.681 --> 01:05:40.227
When I look at you,do you know what I see?

01:05:40.269 --> 01:05:42.563
I see you.

01:05:46.776 --> 01:05:48.819
Your kids are happy,

01:05:48.861 --> 01:05:51.238
you got a new jobthat you love,

01:05:51.280 --> 01:05:53.491
new friends, a senseof community...

01:05:53.532 --> 01:05:56.118
a sense of family...

01:05:56.118 --> 01:05:59.372
and a guy who's crazyabout you.

01:05:59.372 --> 01:06:04.669
You're going to let, what,fear stop all that?

01:06:04.669 --> 01:06:05.961
Olivia, what do you need?

01:06:06.003 --> 01:06:08.464
What can I do?

01:06:08.506 --> 01:06:12.843
Let us happen.

01:06:12.885 --> 01:06:17.556
That fear is real for me.

01:06:17.598 --> 01:06:19.600
I can't.

01:06:19.642 --> 01:06:21.811
I'm sorry.

01:06:28.526 --> 01:06:32.697
Mom, come on, you gotta see this!

